recordedBy: Andrew Salywon; Neil Snow, F. Axelrod
name: Eugenia stewardsonii Britton
locality: Mpio. de Adjuntas. Barrio Guilarte. Few hundred meters up hiking trail to summit, just beyond gazebo.
dynamicProperties: Tree 8 m tall. Infrequent. Most trees partially defoliated, presumably by insects, and in shade of secondary forest. Leaves fragant, smell resembling mint. Bark somewhat rough, brown and gray with patches of green or orange.
